<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	6.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Section&nbsp;7.10(b)(1)&nbsp;of the Plan is hereby amended by replacing it in its entirety to read as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(1)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	An &#147;eligible rollover distribution&#148; is any distribution of all or any portion of the balance to the credit of the &#147;distributee,&#148; except that an &#147;eligible rollover distribution&#148; does not include: any distribution that is one of a series of substantially equal periodic payments (not less frequently than annually) made for the life (or life expectancy) of the &#147;distributee&#148; or the joint lives (or joint life expectancies) of the &#147;distributee&#148; and the &#147;distributee&#146;s&#148; designated beneficiary, or for a specified period of ten years or more; any distribution to the extent such distribution is required under Code Section&nbsp;401(a)(9); the portion of any other distribution that is not includible in gross income (determined without regard to the exclusion for net unrealized appreciation with respect to employer securities); any hardship distribution; and any other distribution that is reasonably expected to total less than $200 during a year.&#160; A portion of a distribution shall not fail to be an &#147;eligible rollover distribution&#148; merely because the portion consists of amounts which are not includible in gross income; provided, however, that such portion which is not includible in gross income may be transferred only to the following &#147;eligible retirement plans&#148;: (A)&nbsp;an individual retirement account or annuity described in Code Section&nbsp;408(a)&nbsp;or (b), (B)&nbsp;a qualified defined contribution plan described in Code Sections 401(a)&nbsp;or 403(a)&nbsp;that agrees to separately account for amounts so transferred, including separately accounting for the portion of such distribution which is includible in gross income and the portion of such distribution which is not so includible, (C)&nbsp;to a qualified trust or to an annuity contract described in Code Section&nbsp;403(b), if such trust or contract provides for separate accounting for amounts so transferred (including interest thereon) including separately accounting for the portion of such distribution which is includable in gross income and the portion of such distribution which is not so includible, or (D)&nbsp;a Roth IRA described in Code Section&nbsp;408A; provided further than any distribution from the Roth Conversion Account or Roth Elective Deferral Account may be transferred only to the following &#147;eligible retirement plans&#148;:&#160; (A)&nbsp;a designated Roth account in a qualified defined contribution plan described in Code Sections 401(a)&nbsp;or a qualified trust or to an annuity contract described in Code Section&nbsp;403(b)&nbsp;or (B)&nbsp;a Roth IRA described in Code Section&nbsp;408A.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	7.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Article&nbsp;XI of the Plan is hereby amended by adding a new Section&nbsp;11.22 to read as follows:
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 75.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:33.0PT;">

	11.22
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Time Limit For Taking Legal Action
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	. Except as specified in ERISA Section&nbsp;413 and regardless of any state or federal laws establishing provisions relating to limitations of actions (except to the extent that such state or federal laws cannot be waived), the following limitations shall apply:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<A NAME="eolPage7"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Eligibility and Participation
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.&#160; No employee, former employee, Participant, Beneficiary or alternate payee (as defined in Code Section&nbsp;414(p)) may take legal or equitable action against the Plan or any of the Plan&#146;s fiduciaries with respect to such employee&#146;s, former employee&#146;s, or Participant&#146;s eligibility to participate in the Plan more than three years after the date of such individual&#146;s termination of employment which immediately follows the service that is the subject of such claim.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Contributions
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.&#160; No Participant, beneficiary or alternate payee (as defined in Code Section&nbsp;414(p)) may take legal or equitable action against the Plan or any of the Plan&#146;s fiduciaries with respect to any Contribution (or alleged missing Contribution) to such Participant&#146;s Account more than three years after the end of the Plan Year for which such Contribution was made (or allegedly should have been made).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Investment Fund Directions and Elections and Allocation of Earnings, Losses and Expenses
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.&#160; No Participant, Beneficiary or alternate payee (as defined in Code Section&nbsp;414(p)) may take legal or equitable action against the Plan or any of the Plan&#146;s fiduciaries with respect to any allocation of any portion of any Participant&#146;s Account to an Investment Fund (or alleged failure to allocate any portion of any Participant&#146;s Account to an Investment Fund) or any earnings or losses of an Investment Fund or other expenses more than three years after the end of the Plan Year for which such allocation was made (or allegedly should have been made) or during which such earnings, losses or expenses occurred.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Other Claims
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.&#160; No employee, former employee, Participant, Beneficiary or alternate payee (as defined in Code Section&nbsp;414(p)) may take legal action against the Plan or any of the Plan&#146;s fiduciaries with respect to any claim not addressed in Section&nbsp;11.22 (a), (b)&nbsp;or (c)&nbsp;above more than one year after the date of the written decision on review provided by the Administrator in accordance with Section&nbsp;11.8.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">

<DIV>
<P ALIGN="RIGHT" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit 10.9.5
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	FIFTH AMENDMENT TO THE
<BR>
	JANUS 401(K)&nbsp;AND EMPLOYEE STOCK OWNERSHIP PLAN
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:36.2PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The Janus 401(k)&nbsp;and Employee Stock Ownership Plan, as amended and restated effective January&nbsp;1, 2014 (the &#147;Plan&#148;), is hereby amended as follows, effective as of September&nbsp;1, 2016, unless otherwise expressly provided below:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	The last sentence of the first paragraph under &#147;Background&#148; is hereby deleted.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Section&nbsp;1.1(h)&nbsp;of the Plan is hereby amended by replacing it in its entirety to read as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(h)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	&#147;Rollover Account&#148; means the account created to hold amounts attributable to Rollover Contributions; provided that any portion of a Participant&#146;s Rollover Contributions that is attributable to after-tax contributions or Roth contributions under Code Section&nbsp;402A shall be accounted for separately from each other and all other contributions accepted as rollovers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Section&nbsp;1.1 of the Plan is hereby amended to add a new subsection (l)&nbsp;to read as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(l)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	&#147;After-Tax Account&#148; means the account created to hold amounts attributable to After-Tax Contributions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Effective July&nbsp;22, 2016, Section&nbsp;1.1 of the Plan is hereby amended to add a new subsection (n)&nbsp;to read as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:38.7PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(n)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	&#147;Stock Dividend Account&#148; means the account created to hold Dividend Contributions reinvested in Company Stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	5.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Section&nbsp;1.8 of the Plan is hereby clarified by deleting the first paragraph and replacing it in its entirety to read as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.8
</FONT>

	&#147;
<U>
	Compensation
</U>
	&#148; means (i)&nbsp;Basic Compensation for purposes of the regular Payroll Withholding Agreement election in Section&nbsp;3.1(a)(2)(i)&nbsp;(including an election with respect to Catch-Up Contributions); (ii)&nbsp;Supplemental Compensation for purposes of the bonus Payroll Withholding Agreement election in Section&nbsp;3.1(a)(2)(ii); (iii)&nbsp;Basic Compensation and Supplemental Compensation for purposes of the passive Payroll Withholding Agreement in Section&nbsp;3.1(b)(1), (iv)&nbsp;Basic Compensation for purposes of the Payroll Withholding Agreement election in Section&nbsp;3.1A;&#160; (v)&nbsp;Basic Compensation and Supplemental Compensation for purposes of Matching Contributions; and (vi)&nbsp;amounts paid to an Eligible Employee by a Participating Employer as &#147;Wages&#148; (defined below) for purposes of other Contributions made under Article&nbsp;IV.

	&#147;Plan,&#148; &#147;Plan and Trust&#148; and &#147;Trust&#148; mean the Janus 401(k)&nbsp;and Employee Stock Ownership Plan (formerly known as the Janus 401(k), Profit Sharing and Employee Stock Ownership Plan). 	3.1A
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	After-Tax Contributions
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.&#160; Each Participant may elect to have an amount deducted from his or her Compensation which would have been received in the Plan Year but for the deduction election, and contributed to the Plan by entering into a Payroll Withholding Agreement to make After-Tax Contributions; provided, that, such Participant&#146;s elected After-Tax Contribution may not exceed 25% of Compensation which would have been received in the Plan Year, but for the contribution election and such election together with his or her Elective Contribution, if any, for a Plan Year may not exceed 75% of Compensation which would have been received in the Plan Year, but for the contribution election(s). When making a deduction election, the Participant must irrevocably designate the contribution as an After-Tax Contribution in the Payroll Withholding Agreement. In the event a Participant fails to designate the contribution as an After-Tax Contribution, the contribution will be deemed to be a Pre-Tax Elective Deferral Contribution.
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Section&nbsp;3.5 of the Plan is hereby amended by replacing it in its entirety to read as follows:
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.5
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Contributions to the Trustee
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.&#160; Pre-Tax Elective Deferral Contributions, Roth Elective Deferral Contributions and/or After-Tax Contributions shall be paid to the Trustee in cash and posted to each Participant&#146;s Accounts as soon as such amounts can reasonably be separated from the Participating Employer&#146;s general assets and balanced against the specific amount made on behalf of each Participant.&#160; However, it is the intention of the Employer that in all events such amounts shall be paid to the Trustee no more than 15 business days following the end of the month that includes the date amounts are deducted from a Participant&#146;s Compensation (or as that maximum period may be otherwise extended by ERISA).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

	The last sentence of Section&nbsp;3.6(a)&nbsp;of the Plan is hereby amended by replacing it in its entirety to read as follows:
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Accounts
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.&#160; The Administrator shall establish and maintain an individual set of Accounts in the name of each Participant and shall record transactions both by type of Account and Investment Fund.&#160; Account values shall be maintained in units for the investment funds and in dollars for the Loan Accounts.&#160; Account values shall be determined as of each Valuation Date. For purposes of this Article&nbsp;V, Participant shall be interpreted to include a Terminated Participant or a Retired Participant, to the extent that any such Terminated Participant or Retired Participant has any vested interest remaining in any of his or her Accounts.

<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">

<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

<FONT FACE="ARIAL">

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	subsequent dividends until a revocation of such election is made by the Participant and received by the Administrator in accordance with the Administrator&#146;s rules&nbsp;and procedures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">

	(4)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	If a Participant fails to make an election for purposes of Section&nbsp;5.8(b)&nbsp;in accordance with such rules&nbsp;and procedures as the Administrator shall prescribe, the Participant will be deemed to have elected for the dividend to be reinvested in Company Stock in accordance with Section&nbsp;5.8(a)(1)(B).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)&nbsp;Treatment of Dividend Contributions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(1)&nbsp; In accordance with Code Section&nbsp;404(k)&nbsp;and the guidance issued thereunder, Dividend Contributions shall not be considered elective deferrals for purposes of Code Section&nbsp;402(g), elective contributions for purposes of Code Section&nbsp;401(k), employee contributions for purposes of Code Section&nbsp;401(m)&nbsp;or annual additions for purposes of Code Section&nbsp;415(c).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:38.5PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(2)&nbsp;Except with respect to Section&nbsp;6.2(h)&nbsp;and Section&nbsp;6.4, amounts in the Stock Dividend Account shall be subject to the terms of the Plan that are applicable to amounts in the ESOP Stock Bonus Account.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

	18.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Section&nbsp;6.1 of the Plan is hereby amended by replacing it in its entirety to read as follows:

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	6.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Elective Contributions, Catch-Up Contributions, After-Tax Contributions and Rollover Contributions
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.&#160; A Participant shall be fully vested in the Participant&#146;s Elective Contributions, Catch-Up Contributions, After-Tax Contributions and Rollover Contributions at all times and no portion of the Participant&#146;s Accounts holding such contribution shall become a Forfeiture for any reason.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	19.

Such recharacterization shall be deemed to occur on the date on which the last Highly Compensated Participant with amounts to be recharacterized is notified of the recharacterization and shall occur no later than the fifteenth day of the third month following the end of each Plan Year to which the recharacterization relates.&#160; The amounts recharacterized as After-Tax Contributions shall be tested as After-Tax Contributions under Section&nbsp;13.3 and shall be treated as After-Tax Contributions for purposes of Code Section&nbsp;72 (regarding the tax treatment of distributions), but the recharacterized amounts shall continue to be treated as Elective Contributions for all other purposes under the Plan.

<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	The first paragraph of Section&nbsp;13.6 of the Plan is hereby amended by replacing it in its entirety to read as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	13.6
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	QACA Safe Harbor Plan Potential
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	. The provisions of this Section&nbsp;13.6 are intended to constitute a &#147;qualified automatic contribution arrangement&#148; (as defined in Code Section&nbsp;401(k)(13)(B)) and shall be construed accordingly for any Plan Year in advance of which the Employer determines that non-elective employer contributions of at least 3% of compensation shall be contributed to the Plan.&#160; For such a Plan Year, the Plan therefore is intended to satisfy the actual deferral percentage and actual contributions percentage tests with respect to the Elective Contributions and the non-elective employer contributions made pursuant to this Section&nbsp;13.6 by virtue of its status as a Code Section&nbsp;401(k)(13) &#147;qualified automatic contribution arrangement&#148; (the &#147;ADP/ACP QACA Safe Harbor Test&#148;) for each Plan Year as to which an appropriate notice has been given.&#160; For
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	each such year, notwithstanding any contrary provision of this Plan, the provisions of Section&nbsp;13.1 through Section&nbsp;13.4 shall be inapplicable with respect to such Elective Contributions and non-elective employer contributions. The following additional requirements shall apply for a Plan Year for which the Plan is intended to satisfy the ADP/ACP QACA Safe Harbor Test:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	If the &#147;annual additions&#148; under the Plan would cause the maximum &#147;annual additions&#148; to be exceeded for any Participant, and all or a portion of the &#147;excess amount&#148; is treated as a Catch-Up Contribution or After-Tax Contribution, then any Matching Contributions which relate to such Catch-Up Contribution or After-Tax Contribution will be used to reduce the Employer contribution in the next &#147;limitation year.&#148;

<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Notwithstanding any provision of this Plan to the contrary, an individual is treated as having been severed from employment during any period the individual is performing service in the uniformed services described in Code Section&nbsp;3401(h)(2)(A)&nbsp;(for purposes of Code Section&nbsp;401(k)(2)(B)(i)(I)).&#160; If an individual elects to receive a distribution by reason of severance from employment, death or disability, the individual may not make an Elective Contribution or After-Tax Contribution during the 6-month period beginning on the date of the distribution.

<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	In addition to Section&nbsp;7.2 and notwithstanding the last sentence of Section&nbsp;7.2(a)&nbsp;and the entirety of Section&nbsp;7.3, the Administrator, pursuant to the election of the Terminated Participant, shall direct the Trustee to commence distribution of any amount under the ESOP Stock Bonus Account and Stock Dividend Account to which the Terminated Participant is entitled no later than one year after the close of the Plan Year in which he or she becomes a Terminated Participant. An election under this Section&nbsp;16.18(a)&nbsp;is subject to Section&nbsp;7.11.
</FONT>

	(2)

<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Unless the Terminated Participant elects otherwise, the distribution of any amount under the ESOP Stock Bonus Account and Stock Dividend Account to which the Terminated Participant is entitled in accordance with a Terminated Participant&#146;s election in Section&nbsp;16.18(a)(1)&nbsp;shall be in substantially equal periodic payments that occur at least annually for a period of no more than five years; provided, that if the amount to which the Terminated Participant is entitled under the Plan exceeds $1,035,000, &#147;five years&#148; will be replace by five years plus one additional year (but not more than five additional years) for each $205,000 or fraction thereof by which the amount to which the Terminated Participant is entitled exceeds $1,035,000. These dollar amounts are adjusted annually in accordance with the method provided in Code Section&nbsp;415(d)&nbsp;pursuant to Regulations.

<A NAME="FIS_EXHIBIT_10_3"></A>
<BR>
<DIV>
<P ALIGN="RIGHT" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit 10.9.6
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	SIXTH AMENDMENT TO THE
<BR>
	JANUS 401(K)&nbsp;AND EMPLOYEE STOCK OWNERSHIP PLAN
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The Janus 401(k)&nbsp;and Employee Stock Ownership Plan, as amended and restated effective January&nbsp;1, 2014 (the &#147;Plan&#148;), is hereby amended as follows, effective as of August&nbsp;31, 2016, unless otherwise expressly provided below:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	The Plan is hereby amended to clarify that the provisions adopted in the Fourth Amendment to implement the new In-Plan Roth Conversion feature and the provisions adopted in the Fifth Amendment to implement the new After-Tax Contributions feature will be effective
<B>
	October&nbsp;3, 2016
</B>
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Section&nbsp;3.1A of the Plan is hereby amended,
<B>
	October&nbsp;3, 2016
</B>
	, by replacing it in its entirety to read as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.1A
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	After-Tax Contributions
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.&#160; Each Participant may elect to have an amount deducted from his or her Compensation which would have been received in the Plan Year but for the deduction election, and contributed to the Plan by entering into a Payroll Withholding Agreement to make After-Tax Contributions; provided, that, such Participant&#146;s elected After-Tax Contribution may not exceed the lesser of (a)&nbsp;25% of Compensation which would have been received in the Plan Year, but for the contribution election and (b)&nbsp;the maximum &#147;annual additions&#148; for the Plan Year as determined under Section&nbsp;14.1(a), less the applicable dollar amount under Code Section&nbsp;402(g)(1)(B)&nbsp;for the Plan Year (as adjusted annually in accordance with the method provided in Code Section&nbsp;402(g)(4)&nbsp;pursuant to Regulations), less the maximum amount of Matching Contributions that may be contributed for a Participant whose annual Compensation equals or exceeds the annual dollar limitation of Code Section&nbsp;401(a)(17) for the Plan Year and whose Elective Contributions for the Plan Year equal the applicable dollar amount under Code Section&nbsp;402(g)(1)(B)&nbsp;for the Plan Year (as adjusted annually in accordance with the method provided in Code Section&nbsp;402(g)(4)&nbsp;pursuant to Regulations).&#160; Further, such After-Tax Contribution election by a Participant together with his or her Elective Contribution, if any, for a Plan Year may not exceed 75% of Compensation which would have been received in the Plan Year, but for the contribution election(s). When making a deduction election, the Participant must irrevocably designate the contribution as an After-Tax Contribution in the Payroll Withholding Agreement. In the event a Participant fails to designate the contribution as an After-Tax Contribution, the contribution will be deemed to be a Pre-Tax Elective Deferral Contribution.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Section&nbsp;10.1 of the Plan is hereby amended, September&nbsp;1, 2016, by replacing it in its entirety to read as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	10.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Voting Company Stock
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.&#160; Each Participant or Beneficiary that has Company Stock allocated to the ESOP Stock Bonus Account or Stock Dividend Account of such Participant or Beneficiary shall have the right to direct the Trustee as to the manner in which the Trustee is to vote (including not vote) that number of shares of Company Stock credited to the Participant&#146;s ESOP Stock Bonus Account and Stock Dividend Account (Vested and not vested).&#160; Directions from a Participant or Beneficiary to the Trustee concerning the voting of Company Stock shall be communicated in writing, or by such other means as agreed to by the Trustee and the Employer.&#160; Upon its receipt of
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	1
</FONT>
<A NAME="A2230904ZEX-10_96_HTM_1124-3-LE_PB_1_090608_7056">
</A>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="100%" NOSHADE ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="COLOR:#010101;">
</DIV>
</DIV>
<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=1,EFW="2230904",CP="JANUS CAPITAL GROUP INC",DN="4",CHK=350906,FOLIO='1',FILE="DISK126:[17ZAA3.17ZAA42403]1124-3-LE_ZAA42403.CHC",USER="CMATTI",CD='FEB 16 11:19 2017' -->
<A NAME="eolPage21"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	the directions, the Trustee shall vote the shares of Company Stock as directed by the Participant or Beneficiary.&#160; Except as otherwise required by law, the Trustee shall vote shares of Company Stock credited to a Participant&#146;s Account for which the Trustee has received no direction from the Participant or Beneficiary in the same proportion on each issue as it votes those shares credited to the Participants&#146; Accounts for which it received voting directions from Participants and Beneficiaries.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Except as otherwise required by law, the Trustee shall vote that number of shares of Company Stock not credited to the Participants&#146; Accounts in the same proportion on each issue as it votes those shares credited to Participants&#146; Accounts for which it received voting directions from Participants and Beneficiaries.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Except as expressly provided herein, the Plan shall remain in full force and effect.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	IN WITNESS WHEREOF, Janus Capital Group Inc. has executed this Amendment as of this 31st day of August&nbsp;2016.
</FONT>
</P>

<BR>
<DIV>
<P ALIGN="RIGHT" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit 10.11.1
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	AMENDMENT NO. 2 TO THE
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	JANUS CAPITAL GROUP INC.
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	AMENDED AND RESTATED INCOME DEFERRAL PROGRAM
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	THIS AMENDMENT (this &#147;Amendment&#148;) to the Amended and Restated Income Deferral Program (as amended through July&nbsp;19, 2010, the &#147;Plan&#148;) is made as of December&nbsp;12, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	WHEREAS, the Administrative Committee (as undersigned below) has been delegated by the Plan Administrator to carry out certain of the Plan Administrator&#146;s responsibilities under the Plan; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	WHEREAS, the Administrative Committee has determined, subject to ratification by the Plan Administrator, to amend the Plan as set forth below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	NOW, THEREFORE, the Plan is hereby amended as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Section&nbsp;2.02 of the Plan is hereby deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#147;
<U>
	Base Compensation
</U>
	: An Eligible Employee&#146;s annual rate of base salary as of the first day of the Plan Year, to the extent paid in U.S. dollars from an Employer&#146;s U.S. payroll, determined before reduction for compensation deferred pursuant to the Plan or any other plan of deferred compensation maintained by an Employer, including, without limitation, any such plan maintained in accordance with Code section 401(k), 125, or 132(f), as determined by the Plan Administrator.&#148;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	The first sentence of Section&nbsp;4.01(a)&nbsp;of the Plan is hereby deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#147;Each Eligible Employee may make an election to defer under the Plan any whole percentage of his or her Base Compensation (up to 70%), Periodic Incentive Compensation (up to 100%), Bonus Compensation (up to 100%), and Equity Compensation (up to 100%) in the manner described in Section&nbsp;4.02.&#148;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	The first sentence of Section&nbsp;4.02(a)&nbsp;of the Plan is hereby deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#147;Subject to the next two sentences, an Eligible Employee must make a deferral election for a Plan Year with respect to Base Compensation by December&nbsp;31
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	st
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	&#160;of the year prior to the beginning of the Plan Year in which the Base Compensation would otherwise be paid.&#148;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	This Amendment shall be governed by, interpreted under and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Delaware.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	5.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Except as modified by this Amendment, the Plan is hereby confirmed in all respects.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV>
<P ALIGN="RIGHT" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit 10.12.2
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	AMENDMENT NO. 2
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	TO THE
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	AMENDED AND RESTATED
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	JANUS CAPITAL GROUP INC.
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	DIRECTOR DEFERRED FEE PLAN
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	THIS AMENDMENT (this &#147;Amendment&#148;) to the Amended and Restated Janus Capital Group Inc. Director Deferred Fee Plan (as amended through December&nbsp;19, 2013, the &#147;Plan&#148;) is made as of December&nbsp;12, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	WHEREAS, the Administrative Committee (as undersigned below) has been delegated by the Plan Administrator to carry out certain of the Plan Administrator&#146;s responsibilities under the Plan; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	WHEREAS, the Administrative Committee has determined, subject to ratification by the Plan Administrator, to amend the Plan as set forth below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	NOW, THEREFORE, the Plan is hereby amended as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	The first sentence of Section&nbsp;4.02(a)&nbsp;of the Plan is hereby deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#147;Deferral of Monetary Fees. Except as set forth below, an Eligible Director must make a deferral election for a Plan Year with respect to Monetary Fees by December&nbsp;31
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	st
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	&#160;of the Plan Year preceding the Plan Year in which the services are performed for which the Monetary Fees would otherwise be paid.&#148;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	The first sentence of Section&nbsp;4.02(b)&nbsp;of the Plan is hereby deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#147;Deferral of Stock Fees. Except as set forth below, an Eligible Director must make a deferral election for a Plan Year with respect to Stock Fees by December&nbsp;31
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	st
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	&#160;of the Plan Year preceding the Plan Year in which the services are performed for which the Stock Fees are granted.&#148;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	This Amendment shall be governed by, interpreted under and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Delaware.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Except as modified by this Amendment, the Plan is hereby confirmed in all respects.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<I>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	[Signature Page&nbsp;Follows]
</FONT>
</I>
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P ALIGN="RIGHT" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit 10.13.9

<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;

</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	JANUS LONG TERM INCENTIVE AWARD (&#147;LTI&#148;) ACCEPTANCE FORM
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The Company grants to &lt;Grantee Name&gt; (&#147;
<U>
	you
</U>
	&#148; or &#147;
<U>
	Grantee
</U>
	&#148;), effective as of &lt;Grant Date&gt; (the &#147;
<U>
	Grant Date
</U>
	&#148;), a Performance Stock Unit Award (the &#147;
<U>
	LTI Award
</U>
	&#148;) as described below, subject to the terms and conditions set forth in this LTI Acceptance Form, the attached Company Plan and the attached Appendices A and B.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Performance Stock Unit Award &#151; see Appendix A for additional terms
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Number of Stock Units Granted
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	&lt;Quantity Granted&gt;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	a.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Pursuant to the terms of the LTI Award, you shall be eligible to vest in a number of stock units, if any, based on the achievement of the performance criteria set forth in
<U>
	Appendix B
</U>
	(the &#147;
<U>
	Performance Criteria
</U>
	&#148;), provided that you have not experienced a Termination of Affiliation prior to &lt;Vesting Date&gt; (the &#147;
<U>
	Vesting Date
</U>
	&#148;).&#160; Any portion of the LTI Award that does not vest because the applicable Performance Criteria have not been satisfied as of the Vesting Date shall be terminated, cancelled and forfeited.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	b.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Notwithstanding the provisions of (a)&nbsp;above and (c)&nbsp;below, if you have a Termination of Affiliation with the Company due to death or Disability, the LTI Award shall vest based on achievement of the Performance Criteria measured as of the last trading date prior to the Termination of Affiliation (determined using the average closing stock price for the shares of the Company&#146;s common stock for the ninety (90) trading day period immediately preceding the Termination of Affiliation). Except as provided in the preceding sentence or in (c)&nbsp;below, in the event that you have a Termination of Affiliation, any portion of the LTI Award that is unvested, and any of your rights hereunder, shall be terminated, cancelled and forfeited effective immediately upon such Termination of Affiliation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	c.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in the Company Plan, following a Change of Control, the LTI Award shall remain outstanding, the Performance Period shall remain in effect, and you shall be eligible to vest in a number of stock units, if any, based on the achievement of the Performance Criteria as set forth in Appendix B, provided that you have not experienced a Termination of Affiliation prior to the Vesting Date.&#160; Notwithstanding the foregoing and the provisions of (a)&nbsp;above, in the event that you experience a Termination of Affiliation due to the&#160; termination of your employment or service by the Company without Cause or by you for Good Reason, in each case following a Change of Control and prior to &lt;Vesting Date&gt;, the LTI Award shall vest based on achievement of the Performance Criteria measured as of the last trading date prior to the Termination of Affiliation (determined using the average closing stock price for the shares of the Company&#146;s common stock&#160; for the ninety (90) trading day period immediately preceding the Termination of Affiliation).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	d.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	In accordance with the Company Plan, the Committee may, in its sole discretion, accelerate the vesting of all or a portion of the LTI Award or waive any or all of the terms and conditions applicable to this LTI Acceptance Form&nbsp;or the attached Appendices. This LTI Acceptance Form&nbsp;and the attached Appendices do not supersede, or otherwise amend
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

In the event you fail to return the executed original within sixty (60) days, the Company reserves the right to terminate and forfeit the LTI Award (including any rights provided for in this LTI Acceptance Form&nbsp;and the attached Appendices), or to suspend or forfeit all or any vesting event(s)&nbsp;arising from the LTI Award. This LTI Acceptance Form&nbsp;may be executed in counterparts, which together shall constitute one and the same original. This LTI Acceptance Form&nbsp;may be executed by the exchange of facsimile signature pages, provided that by doing so the Participant agrees to provide an original signature as soon thereafter as possible.

	APPENDIX A &#151; TERMS OF PERFORMANCE STOCK UNIT AWARD

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Grant of Performance Stock Unit Award
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Subject to the provisions of this Appendix, the LTI Acceptance Form&nbsp;and the Company&#146;s 2010 Long Term Incentive Stock Plan, as may be amended from time to time (the &#147;
<U>
	Company Plan
</U>
	&#148;), the Company hereby grants to Grantee the number of performance stock units (the &#147;
<U>
	Stock Units
</U>
	&#148;) identified under the Performance Stock Unit Award section of the attached LTI Acceptance Form, representing the same number of shares of the Company&#146;s common stock, par value $.01 per share (&#147;
<U>
	Common Stock
</U>
	&#148;).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	No Right to Continued Employment
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Nothing in this Appendix or the Company Plan shall confer upon Grantee any right to continue providing services to, or be in the employ of, the Company or any Subsidiary or interfere in any way with the right of the Company or any Subsidiary to terminate Grantee&#146;s association or employment at any time.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Unfair Interference
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	During Grantee&#146;s employment with the Company or any Subsidiary and during the twelve (12) months after Termination of Affiliation, Grantee shall not: (i)&nbsp;knowingly and directly solicit, hire or attempt to hire, or assist another in soliciting, hiring or attempting to hire, on behalf of any Competitive Business, any person who is an employee or contractor of the Company or any Subsidiary; or (ii)&nbsp;knowingly and directly divert, attempt to divert, solicit, or assist another in diverting, attempting to divert or soliciting, the customer business of any Protected Client on behalf of a Competitive Business.&#160; For purposes of this section, &#147;
<U>
	Competitive Business
</U>
	&#148; means any business that provides investment advisory or investment management services or related services; and &#147;
<U>
	Protected Client
</U>
	&#148; shall mean any person or entity to whom the Company or any Subsidiary provided investment advisory or investment management services at any point during the six (6)&nbsp;months preceding Grantee&#146;s Termination of Affiliation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

<U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Change of Control
</FONT>
</U>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	For purposes of this Appendix and the LTI Acceptance Form, &#147;
<U>
	Good Reason
</U>
	&#148; shall have the meaning assigned to such term in Grantee&#146;s individual employment, change in control or severance agreement (if any).&#160; If Grantee is not a party to an agreement in which Good Reason is defined, Good Reason shall mean the occurrence of any of the events or conditions described below which are not cured by the Company within thirty (30) days after the Company has received written notice from Grantee (which notice must be provided by Grantee within ninety (90) days of the initial existence of the event or condition constituting Good Reason):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	a material adverse alteration in the nature or status of your responsibilities from those in effect immediately prior to the Change of Control other than any such alteration primarily attributable to the fact that the Company may no longer be a public company or to other changes in the identity, nature
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

	the relocation of Grantee&#146;s principal place of employment to a location more than forty (40) miles from Grantee&#146;s principal place of employment immediately prior to the Change of Control, provided that such relocation results in a material negative change to Grantee&#146;s employment.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT FACE="ARIAL">
	Notwithstanding subsection (c)&nbsp;of the LTI Acceptance Form, in the event of a Change of Control of the Company, the Company may, in its sole discretion, cancel Grantee&#146;s LTI Award in exchange for a payment in cash in an amount equal to (x)&nbsp;the consideration paid per share of Common Stock in the Change of Control multiplied by (y)&nbsp;the number of shares of Common Stock subject to Grantee&#146;s LTI Award that vest based on achievement of the Performance Criteria measured as of the last trading date prior to the Change in Control (determined using the average closing stock price for the shares of the Company&#146;s common stock&#160; for the ninety (90) trading day period immediately preceding the Change in Control).

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIAL" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Appendix, the LTI Acceptance Form, the Company Plan or Appendix B, and subject to then-applicable U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, New York Stock Exchange and/or other regulatory requirements related to clawback or compensation reimbursement rules, if Grantee is found by a court of competent jurisdiction (in a final judgment that is either not appealed or is non-appealable) or by any relevant regulator to have knowingly committed fraud against the Company or any of its Affiliates, or if Grantee is found to have actively participated in, knowingly concealed or covered up, or knowingly failed to identify a material misstatement in the Company&#146;s financial statements, Grantee&#146;s LTI awards granted in the three (3)&nbsp;calendar years prior to such judgment or regulatory determination, whether vested or unvested, shall be immediately forfeited and cancelled, and Grantee shall promptly return and repay to the Company, in respect of any shares of Common Stock, stock options or mutual fund units previously transferred to Grantee pursuant to such LTI award agreements, an amount equal to the lesser of: (i)&nbsp;the fair market value of such shares, stock options (based on the intrinsic value of such stock options) or mutual fund units on the date of vesting, and (ii)&nbsp;the fair market value of such shares, stock options (based on the intrinsic value of such stock options) or mutual fund units on the date on which such repayment obligation arises, in each case, regardless of whether Grantee previously sold or otherwise disposed of such shares.
